I also found that the define() function blocks forever--the examples in the documentation that use define() for custom namespaces don't work as intended.  There is a function named ```_should_stop_waiting()``` in ```__init__.py``` that references the variable ```_connected```, but the variable does not exist:

```python
    def _should_stop_waiting(self, for_connect=False, for_callbacks=False):
        if for_connect:
            for namespace in self._namespace_by_path.values():
                is_namespace_connected = getattr(
                    namespace, '_connected', False)
```

If you remove the third parameter (False) from the getattr() call, an exception will occur because the BaseNamespace (SocketIONamespace) does not have an attribute named ```_connected```, and getattr() is masking that fact.  Is there possibly an update to ```namespaces.py``` that didn't get committed when the lines above were added to ```_should_stop_waiting()```?

