@stephanie-wang ,
1. that's right. This PR spills over placeable tasks only. There are other cases/race conditions where you'd like to spill over ready tasks. I wanted to add that as part of a future PR, because it starts getting into the spillback policy, to answer the question: "which ready tasks does it make sense to spill"? 
2. yes it will, I added a call to ScheduleTasks when we handle GetTask from the worker. This works because the policy is now aware of the raylet's load, checking task.request <= node.avail - node.load, and all ready tasks count against the load. So we can now safely invoke the scheduling policy on self followed by dispatch. Good question, though.

